question:
What is the output of the following code snippet?
class A {
    A() { System.out.print("A"); }
}
class B extends A {
    B() { System.out.print("B"); }
    B(int val) { System.out.print("B" + val); }
}
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        B obj = new B(5);
    }
}

Given the code below, what is the result of creating an instance of ClassC?
class ClassA {
    ClassA() { System.out.println("ClassA Constructor"); }
}
class ClassB extends ClassA {
    ClassB() {
        this(10);
        System.out.println("ClassB No-arg Constructor");
    }
    ClassB(int i) {
        System.out.println("ClassB Parameterized Constructor: " + i);
    }
}
class ClassC extends ClassB {
    ClassC() {
        super(20);
        System.out.println("ClassC Constructor");
    }
}
